1. Software Development Kit (SDK) is a collection of software development tools in one installable package.
   SDK facilitates the creation of applications by having compilers, debuggers and perhaps a software framework[1].
2. Integrated Development Environment (IDE) is a software application that provides comprehensive facilities to
   computer programmer for software development. An IDE commonly consists of at least a source code editor, build
   automation tools and a debugger[1].
3. IDEs used for Java programming: eclipse, IntelliJ IDEA, or Netbeans.
4. Java Development Kit (JDK): is an implementation of either one of the Java Platform, Standard Edition, Java Platform,
   Enterprise Edition, or Java platform, Micro Editio paltforms released by Oracle Corporation in the form of a binary
   product aimed at Java developers on Solaris, Linux, macOS or Windows[1].

[1] https://en.wikipedia.org
